From adb1ee4de04d496f3da409bb6791cfdd744ab2c3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kees Cook <kees@kernel.org>
Date: Tue, 11 Mar 2025 15:56:05 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] wifi: virt_wifi: Add __nonstring annotations for unterminated strings
Git-commit: adb1ee4de04d496f3da409bb6791cfdd744ab2c3
Patch-mainline: v6.15-rc1
References: jsc#PED-14425

When a character array without a terminating NUL character has a static
initializer, GCC 15's -Wunterminated-string-initialization will only
warn if the array lacks the "nonstring" attribute[1]. Mark the arrays
with __nonstring to and correctly identify the char array as "not a C
string" and thereby eliminate the warning.

Link: https://gcc.gnu.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=117178 [1]
Signed-off-by: Kees Cook <kees@kernel.org>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20250311225604.it.926-kees@kernel.org
Signed-off-by: Johannes Berg <johannes.berg@intel.com>
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 drivers/net/wireless/virtual/virt_wifi.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/virtual/virt_wifi.c b/drivers/net/wireless/virtual/virt_wifi.c
index f9d11a023313..1fffeff2190c 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/virtual/virt_wifi.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/virtual/virt_wifi.c
@@ -146,7 +146,7 @@ static void virt_wifi_inform_bss(struct wiphy *wiphy)
 	static const struct {
 		u8 tag;
 		u8 len;
-		u8 ssid[8];
+		u8 ssid[8] __nonstring;
 	} __packed ssid = {
 		.tag = WLAN_EID_SSID,
 		.len = VIRT_WIFI_SSID_LEN,
-- 
2.53.0

